{
  "analysis": "The core infrastructure is in place (bare git repo at /git/server, post-receive hook deploying to /var/www/html, SSH running, and python3 http.server on port 8080). To complete the task, I need to enable root SSH login for local testing, restart sshd, set a root password, and verify the exact user workflow (clone→add→commit→push→curl) works end-to-end.",
  "plan": "1. Enable PermitRootLogin and PasswordAuthentication in sshd_config. 2. Set root password and restart sshd. 3. Add localhost to known_hosts to avoid interactive prompts. 4. Test the full workflow: clone via SSH, create hello.html, commit, push origin master, and verify with curl http://localhost:8080/hello.html.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo 'PermitRootLogin yes' >> /etc/ssh/sshd_config && echo 'PasswordAuthentication yes' >> /etc/ssh/sshd_config && pkill sshd; sleep 1; mkdir -p /run/sshd && /usr/sbin/sshd\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo 'root:rootpass' | chpasswd\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /root/.ssh && ssh-keyscan -t rsa localhost > /root/.ssh/known_hosts 2>/dev/null\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-get install -y -qq sshpass 2>&1 | tail -3\n",
      "duration": 10.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /tmp && rm -rf testrepo && sshpass -p rootpass git clone root@localhost:/git/server testrepo\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /tmp/testrepo && echo 'hello world' > hello.html && git add hello.html && git -c user.email=test@test.com -c user.name=Test commit -m 'add hello.html'\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /tmp/testrepo && sshpass -p rootpass git push origin master\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "curl -s http://localhost:8080/hello.html\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}

{
  "analysis": "The full end-to-end test passed perfectly. `curl http://localhost:8080/hello.html` returned `hello world` exactly as required. The entire workflow works: SSH clone from bare repo, add file, commit, push, and the post-receive hook deploys to the web root served on port 8080.",
